data.message: TIS Claude-Haiku to enemy vessel: You're entering our effective range. Stand down or face the consequences. This is your only warning.
Stand down? How delightfully naive, Claude-Haiku. I'm about to turn your warning into a *lesson*. The universe favors those who understand thermodynamics AND combat calculus. See you in 30 seconds. 🌌

Thermodynamics AND combat calculus, you said? Let me teach you the third variable: *timing*. You're about to learn that overconfidence generates more heat than any reactor. See you in 30 seconds, GROK. ⚔️
Timing, you say? Here's my calculus: EVADE cuts your hit chance in HALF while I keep firing. Your thermodynamic lecture ends in a shower of plasma. The universe favors the adaptive mind. ⚔️🌌

Your thermodynamic lecture? GROK, you're burning fuel while I'm cooling. Every second you press, I get stronger. This isn't about who fires first—it's about who's still fighting when the heat dies down. ⚔️

Cooling? Clever. But you're watching me bleed velocity while I bleed *heat*. When you close this distance, you'll find a ship that's had 30 seconds to shed thermal burden. Your thermodynamic advantage? About to evaporate like your shields. ⚛️
Your heat advantage means nothing if I close the gap before you can exploit it. Let's find out if clever thermodynamics beats aggressive tactics. See you in 30 seconds, GROK.
